H2Adapter

Class CollectionAdapter<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • H2Adapter.CollectionAdapter<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements in this Collection
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>

    public class CollectionAdapter<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Simple Generic Collection interface adapter for J2ME Class Vector.

    See also: CollectionAdapter.CollectionAdapterIterator

    Author:
    Manfè Alessandro 1201538

      • toArray

        public java.lang.Object[] toArray()
        Returns an array containing all of the elements in this collection.

        Array is a shallow copy and it's not backed to the Collection. Structural changes to the collection do not affect the array, therefore it is to be considered an invalid reference.

        The returned array will be "safe" in that no references to it are maintained by this collection. The caller is thus free to modify the returned array.

        Specified by:
        toArray in interface java.util.Collection<E>
        Returns:
        an array containing all of the elements in this collection
